cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CY 

This paper primarily focuses on the security aspects of process accounting logs and their potential use in identifying masqueraders on HPC clusters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of a software tool (NVision-PA) for statistical analysis of command behavior, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also uses statistical analysis techniques, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of process accounting logs and statistical analysis for monitoring and managing legitimate workloads in HPC environments could fall under the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
